article.headline: Albany (NY) 82, Dartmouth 74
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Gerardo Suero scored 23 points, his eighth game of 20-plus points this season, to help Albany (N.Y.) down Dartmouth 82-74 on Friday to stay undefeated at home. Mike Black added 20 points, Logan Aronhalt 15 and Luke Devlin 11 for the Great Danes (7-5), who have won all six contests at home this season. Albany has won back-to-back games for the second time this season. Albany evened the all-time series against Dartmouth at four wins apiece in a game that was easy throughout for the Great Danes, who led the entire way. The Great Danes used an 8-0 run midway through the opening half to carry a 46-31 advantage into the break. Albany won despite being outscored by Dartmouth 43-36 in the second half. Jabari Trotter scored 22 points to lead the Big Green (3-10), R.J. Griffin added 12 and Jvonte Brooks 11. Dartmouth has lost three straight.
